'''''A Little Lumpen Novelita''''' (''Una novelita lumpen'' in Spanish) is a novel by the Chilean author [[Roberto Bola<U+00F1>o]]. A translation from the Spanish by [[Natasha Wimmer]] is forthcoming from [[New Directions Publishing|New Directions]] in September 2014.{{fact|date=May 2014}}

The book is divided into sixteen short chapters, told in first person by the protagonist Bianca, who recalls her childhood, adolescence and early adulthood.

''[[Il Futuro]]'', a 2013 film directed by Alicia Scherson and starring [[Manuela Martelli]] and [[Rutger Hauer]], was based on this novel.{{fact|date=May 2014}}
